    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Pick your <strong>basil leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop the<strong> stalks</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-polpette-with-tomato-and-basil-broth/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> mince</strong> with the <strong>chopped basil stalks</strong> (save the leaves for later!) and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix until combined (clean hands is the best way), then roll into 3 meatballs per person</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-polpette-with-tomato-and-basil-broth/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> and cook for 4 min, turning occasionally with tongs until browned on all sides</p><p>Once browned, set aside on a plate (reserve the pan) \u2013 these are your<strong> polpette</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-polpette-with-tomato-and-basil-broth/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-polpette-with-tomato-and-basil-broth/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong>,<strong> dried basil</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir until combined, then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, add your<strong> giant couscous</strong> and cook for 5 min or until beginning to soften \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato & basil broth</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-polpette-with-tomato-and-basil-broth/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>basil leaves</strong> roughly (save some for garnish!)</p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-polpette-with-tomato-and-basil-broth/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> polpette</strong> to the <strong>tomato & basil broth</strong> and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-polpette-with-tomato-and-basil-broth/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the pan from the heat and stir the <strong>chopped basil</strong> through</p><p>Serve the <strong>tomato & basil broth</strong> in a bowl topped with the<strong> polpette</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>basil leaves</strong> and sprinkle with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
